My Bishop is already where I want it and this pawn wasn't doing much. Perhaps I should have let it be then if black was to capture with dxc then I would have a nice pin on his king and only one pawn would be supporting the knight on e4.

Yes a bishop pair is a good thing however in this case to save the bishop I need to move it to the awkward c1. Besides this bishop isn't doing much at the moment yet blacks knight is doing more. Should I entice black to take with Nxc3 then Get a nice solid pawn structure and a shiny new open file to play with.

!? I wasn't sure about this move I felt it was just pawn grabbing as it was. I realised black had the option of Bxf3 gxf3Qxf3 winning back the pawn. After a while looking at the position I thought I could get away with this further consolidating my advantage with Rg1?? and a checkmate threat. It's not till I made the move that I realised this wouldn't work since after Bxf3 gxf3 Rg1?? fails since Blacks queen would have the rook protecting it allowing for Qxf2+!.
This is the only move really. As I outlined earlier I can't make the move Rg1 like I would have liked to.

This is not the best move in this position. Better was Qc4+ the computer lists the following sequence of moves.  Qc4+ Rf7 23. d7 Rd8 24. Rd1 Qb7 25. Rg1 Rdxd7 26. e4 Kh8 27. Rxd7 Qxd7 28. exf5 Re7+ 29. Kf1 Qxf5
Where I can once again use the bank rank theme as well As the g7 weakness to great effect.
